  "What is an antiderivative of a function?": "",
  "The function evaluated at x = 0": "",
  "The reciprocal of the derivative": "",
  "A function F(x) whose derivative equals the given function: F'(x) = f(x)": "",
  "The derivative of the given function": "",
  "An antiderivative of f(x) is any function F(x) such that F'(x) = f(x). Antidifferentiation is the reverse process of differentiation.": "",
  "What does the 'constant of integration' C represent?": "",
  "The coefficient of the highest power term": "",
  "An arbitrary constant added because infinitely many antiderivatives exist, differing only by a constant": "",
  "A specific number that must be calculated": "",
  "The value of the function at x = 0": "",
  "The constant of integration C accounts for the fact that if F(x) is an antiderivative of f(x), then so is F(x) + C for any constant C. Since the derivative of a constant is zero, all antiderivatives differ by at most a constant.": "",
  "What does the integral sign and 'dx' indicate in an indefinite integral?": "",
  "The integral sign means summation and dx means delta-x": "",
  "The integral sign indicates antidifferentiation and 'dx' specifies x as the variable of integration": "",
  "They are just decorative notation with no meaning": "",
  "The integral sign means derivative and dx means with respect to x": "",
  "The elongated S (integral sign) indicates that we are finding an antiderivative (reversing differentiation). The dx tells us that x is the variable of integration and reminds us of the Leibniz notation for differentials.": "",
  "What is the 'power rule for integration'?": "",
  "Integral of x^n dx = x^(n+1) + C for all n": "",
  "Integral of x^n dx = x^(n+1)/(n+1) + C, valid for n not equal to -1": "",
  "Integral of x^n dx = x^n/n + C": "",
  "Integral of x^n dx = nx^(n-1) + C": "",
  "The power rule for integration states: integral of x^n dx = x^(n+1)/(n+1) + C, provided n is not -1. When n = -1, the integral is ln|x| + C instead.": "",
  "What is an 'indefinite integral'?": "",
  "An integral that cannot be evaluated without accounting for additional influences": "",
  "The general antiderivative of a function, written as integral of f(x) dx = F(x) + C, without specified limits": "",
  "An integral with infinite limits according to widely held views on this topic": "",
  "The derivative of a function, even when conditions shift significantly": "",
  "An indefinite integral represents the family of all antiderivatives of a function. It has no limits of integration and always includes the constant C to represent the entire family F(x) + C.": "",
  "What does 'general antiderivative' mean?": "",
  "The antiderivative with C = 0": "",
  "The most common antiderivative": "",
  "The family of all antiderivatives of a function, expressed as F(x) + C where C is an arbitrary constant": "",
  "An antiderivative that works for all functions": "",
  "The general antiderivative F(x) + C represents every possible antiderivative of f(x). Each specific value of C gives a particular antiderivative, and together they form a family of curves that are vertical translations of each other.": "",
  "What is a 'particular antiderivative'?": "",
  "A specific antiderivative obtained by choosing a particular value for the constant C, often using an initial condition": "",
  "The derivative of a particular function": "",
  "An antiderivative that only works for particular functions": "",
  "An antiderivative with no constant": "",
  "A particular antiderivative is one specific member of the family F(x) + C, determined by an initial condition such as F(a) = b. This pins down the exact value of C.": "",
  "What is meant by 'initial condition' when finding antiderivatives?": "",
  "The derivative at t = 0": "",
  "The first step of integration": "",
  "A known value of the antiderivative at a specific point, used to determine the constant C": "",
  "The lower limit of a definite integral": "",
  "An initial condition like F(0) = 5 provides enough information to determine the constant C in the general antiderivative F(x) + C. Substituting the known values and solving for C gives the particular solution.": "",
  "What is the 'sum and difference rule' for indefinite integrals?": "",
  "The sum of two integrals always equals zero": "",
  "The integral of a product equals the product of the integrals": "",
  "Sums cannot be integrated term by term": "",
  "The integral of a sum (or difference) equals the sum (or difference) of the integrals": "",
  "The sum/difference rule states: integral of [f(x) +/- g(x)] dx = integral of f(x) dx +/- integral of g(x) dx. This allows us to integrate polynomials and sums term by term.": "",
  "What does 'antidifferentiation' mean?": "",
  "Taking the derivative of a function": "",
  "The process of finding a function whose derivative is the given function; the reverse of differentiation": "",
  "Finding the difference between antiderivatives": "",
  "Evaluating a definite integral": "",
  "Antidifferentiation is the process of finding an antiderivative (indefinite integral). Given f(x), antidifferentiation seeks F(x) such that F'(x) = f(x). It is the inverse operation of differentiation.": "",
  "A ball is thrown upward with initial velocity 48 ft/s from a height of 64 ft. Its acceleration is a(t) = -32 ft/s^2. Find the position function s(t).": "",
  "s(t) = -16t^2 + 64": "",
  "s(t) = -16t^2 + 48t": "",
  "s(t) = -16t^2 + 48t + 64": "",
  "s(t) = -32t^2 + 48t + 64": "",
  "First, v(t) = integral of -32 dt = -32t + C1. Since v(0) = 48, C1 = 48, so v(t) = -32t + 48. Then s(t) = integral of (-32t + 48) dt = -16t^2 + 48t + C2. Since s(0) = 64, C2 = 64. So s(t) = -16t^2 + 48t + 64.": "",
  "A car decelerates at a(t) = -6t m/s^2. If its initial velocity is 54 m/s, find the velocity function and determine when the car stops.": "",
  "v(t) = -3t^2 + 54; car stops at t = 6 seconds": "",
  "v(t) = -6t^2 + 54; car stops at t = 3 seconds": "",
  "v(t) = -3t^2 + 54; car stops at t = sqrt(18) seconds": "",
  "v(t) = -6t + 54; car stops at t = 9 seconds": "",
  "v(t) = integral of -6t dt = -3t^2 + C. Since v(0) = 54, C = 54, so v(t) = -3t^2 + 54. The car stops when v(t) = 0: -3t^2 + 54 = 0, t^2 = 18, t = sqrt(18) = 3sqrt(2) seconds.": "",
  "A company's marginal cost function is C'(x) = 0.6x + 20 dollars per unit, and the fixed cost is $500. Find the total cost of producing 100 units.": "",
  "$3500": "",
  "$5000": "",
  "$5500": "",
  "$80": "",
  "C(x) = integral of (0.6x + 20) dx = 0.3x^2 + 20x + K. Since C(0) = 500 (fixed cost), K = 500. C(100) = 0.3(10000) + 20(100) + 500 = 3000 + 2000 + 500 = $5500.": "",
  "A patient receives medication that is absorbed at a rate of R(t) = 12e^(-0.3t) mg/hr. If the initial amount in the bloodstream is 5 mg, find the amount at time t = 2 hours.": "",
  "40(1 - e^(-0.6)) mg": "",
  "5 + 40(1 - e^(-0.6)) mg": "",
  "17 mg": "",
  "5 + 12e^(-0.6) mg": "",
  "A(t) = integral of 12e^(-0.3t) dt = -40e^(-0.3t) + C. A(0) = -40 + C = 5, so C = 45. A(t) = 45 - 40e^(-0.3t). At t = 2: A(2) = 45 - 40e^(-0.6) = 5 + 40(1 - e^(-0.6)).": "",
  "Water flows into a tank at rate R(t) = 4t^3 gallons per minute. If the tank initially contains 10 gallons, how much water is in the tank after 3 minutes?": "",
  "108 gallons": "",
  "81 gallons": "",
  "91 gallons": "",
  "118 gallons": "",
  "W(t) = integral of 4t^3 dt = t^4 + C. W(0) = 0 + C = 10, so C = 10. W(3) = 81 + 10 = 91 gallons.": "",
  "A rocket has acceleration a(t) = 6t + 10 m/s^2. If it starts from rest at ground level, find its height at t = 4 seconds.": "",
  "128 meters": "",
  "144 meters": "",
  "104 meters": "",
  "200 meters": "",
  "v(t) = integral of (6t + 10) dt = 3t^2 + 10t + C1. v(0) = 0, so C1 = 0. s(t) = integral of (3t^2 + 10t) dt = t^3 + 5t^2 + C2. s(0) = 0, so C2 = 0. s(4) = 64 + 80 = 144 meters.": "",
  "A population grows at a rate of P'(t) = 100 + 20t individuals per year. If the initial population is 5000, what is the population after 10 years?": "",
  "6000 individuals": "",
  "6500 individuals": "",
  "8000 individuals": "",
  "7000 individuals": "",
  "P(t) = integral of (100 + 20t) dt = 100t + 10t^2 + C. P(0) = C = 5000. P(10) = 1000 + 1000 + 5000 = 7000 individuals.": "",
  "An object's velocity is v(t) = 3 cos(t) m/s and its initial position is s(0) = 2 meters. What is the position function?": "",
  "s(t) = 3 sin(t) + 2": "",
  "s(t) = 3 sin(t)": "",
  "s(t) = -3 sin(t) + 2": "",
  "s(t) = 3 cos(t) + 2": "",
  "s(t) = integral of 3 cos(t) dt = 3 sin(t) + C. Using s(0) = 2: 3 sin(0) + C = 2, so C = 2. Therefore s(t) = 3 sin(t) + 2.": "",
  "A factory's revenue rate is R'(x) = 500 - 2x dollars per unit. If R(0) = 0, find the revenue from selling 50 units.": "",
  "$25,000": "",
  "$400": "",
  "$22,500": "",
  "$20,000": "",
  "R(x) = integral of (500 - 2x) dx = 500x - x^2 + C. R(0) = 0, so C = 0. R(50) = 500(50) - 2500 = 25000 - 2500 = $22,500.": "",
  "A heating element warms a room at rate T'(t) = 8/(t+1) degrees per hour. If the room starts at 60 degrees, what is the temperature after 3 hours?": "",
  "68 degrees": "",
  "60 + 8 ln(3) degrees": "",
  "60 + 24 degrees": "",
  "60 + 8 ln(4) degrees": "",
  "T(t) = integral of 8/(t+1) dt = 8 ln|t+1| + C. T(0) = 8 ln(1) + C = C = 60. T(3) = 8 ln(4) + 60 = 60 + 8 ln(4) degrees.": ""
